description: This file defines the interface and mock/implementation class for Bluetooth control functionalities in a WPEFramework plugin. It includes method declarations for managing Bluetooth discoverability, scanning, connection, pairing, device management, and event registration. The file also contains namespace structures, versioning info, and event notification helpers.

classes.name: JSONRPCImplementation
classes.description: Sample stub implementation class for Bluetooth control commands, providing methods for discoverability, scanning, device connection, pairing, and device info management.

methods.name: Register
methods.description: Registers Bluetooth control methods and properties with the JSONRPC module, enabling remote procedure calls and event subscriptions.

methods.name: Unregister
methods.description: Unregisters Bluetooth control methods and properties from the JSONRPC module.

methods.name: Event.DiscoverableStarted
methods.description: Triggers the 'discoverablestarted' event, notifying clients that Bluetooth device is now discoverable.

methods.name: Event.ScanStarted
methods.description: Triggers the 'scanstarted' event, indicating Bluetooth device scanning has started.

methods.name: Event.DeviceStateChanged
methods.description: Notifies clients of changes in Bluetooth device state, such as connection or pairing status.

methods.name: Event.PINCodeRequest
methods.description: Informs clients that a PIN code input is requested for pairing.

methods.name: Event.PasskeyRequest
methods.description: Informs clients that a passkey is requested for authentication.

methods.name: Event.PasskeyConfirmRequest
methods.description: Informs clients that confirmation of a passkey is required.
